txt.en: 'The dredging machines in the Gladden Fields unearthed many items from the swamp, [placeholder]: weapons, armour-pieces, and other trinkets. Some of these have made their way to Kidzul-kâlah, and it offends me to think that brooches and jewels of personal significance were removed from those who perished wearing them. Reclaim these, if you can.'
Brooches of the fallen have been taken to Kidzul-kâlah, and should be reclaimed from those who deserve them not.
Hithril of the Elves of Lórien is concerned about the shadowy waters that surround the sunken ruins of Kidzul-kâlah.
